Let f<sub>1</sub> : R $$ \to $$ R, f<sub>2</sub> : [0, $$\infty $$) $$ \to $$ R, f<sub>3</sub> : R $$ \to $$ R, and f<sub>4</sub> : R $$ \to $$ [0, $$\infty $$) be defined by
<p>$${f_1}\left( x \right) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {\left| x \right|} &amp; {if\,x &lt; 0,}  \cr 
   {{e^x}} &amp; {if\,x \ge 0;}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$</p>
<p>f<sub>2</sub>(x) = x<sup>2</sup> ;</p>
$${f_3}\left( x \right) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {\sin x} &amp; {if\,x &lt; 0,}  \cr 
   x &amp; {if\,x \ge 0;}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$
<p>and</p>
<p>$${f_4}\left( x \right) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {{f_2}\left( {{f_1}\left( x \right)} \right)} &amp; {if\,x &lt; 0,}  \cr 
   {{f_2}\left( {{f_1}\left( x \right)} \right) - 1} &amp; {if\,x \ge 0;}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$</p>
